Use the standard library

This is how to string_to_md5 of text:
   Remember that out is []

   When text is "", then:
      The answer is out
   End when

   When text is "Hello world", then:
      The answer is "3e25960a79dbc69b674cd4ec67a72c62"
   End when

   When text is "A B C", then:
      The answer is "0ef78513b0cb8cef12743f5aeb35f888"
   End when

   The answer is out
Now you know

>>> string_to_md5 of ""
[]
>>> string_to_md5 of "Hello world"
"3e25960a79dbc69b674cd4ec67a72c62"
>>> string_to_md5 of "A B C"
"0ef78513b0cb8cef12743f5aeb35f888"